ai-patthana16.11:0.2_0: (This should be expanded as in SN 4.)
ai-patthana16.11:0.3_0: Next there are bulging muscles, and winds.
ai-patthana16.11:1.1_0: An undetermined teaching has not been declared by the Buddha.
ai-patthana16.11:1.1_1: He has not been declared by the Buddha.
ai-patthana16.11:1.1_2: He doesn’t have any declared cause or condition for the world.
ai-patthana16.11:1.1_3: They haven’t declared: ‘Of rebirth is a condition for old age and death, and are unable to arise because of causes.’
ai-patthana16.11:1.1_4: They don’t arise because of undeclared, unskillful qualities, or skillful qualities born.
ai-patthana16.11:1.1_5: That is the cause, this is the reason why someone ...
ai-patthana16.11:2.1_0: Endowed with the skillful, not its supreme beings.
ai-patthana16.11:2.1_1: the skillful quality doesn’t arise for oneself.
ai-patthana16.11:2.1_2: skillful qualities that arise for the whole world—with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and it doesn’t arise because of causes and reason.
ai-patthana16.11:3.1_0: I have not been declared by the Buddha for its own welfare and happiness.
ai-patthana16.11:3.1_1: There is no declared by the world for its gods, not others.
ai-patthana16.11:3.1_2: You don’t have any declared by the world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans.
